-- Kumba Workers Start Strike Over Salaries, Management Considering Response
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-10-04T06:17:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/kumba-workers-start-strike-over-salaries-management-considering-response.html
Workers at Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.
started a strike over a pay, the National Union of Mineworkers
said.  There has been a “massive turnout” following the strike
call, Lesiba Seshoka, the labor union’s spokesman, said in a
phone interview today. Management of the company and unions will
meet today over the strike, he said.  Kumba’s management is still evaluating its response to the
strike, company spokesman Gert Schoeman said by phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
